{"type":"freeform","cover":{"titleText":"","subTitleText":"","presenterText":"","dateText":"","logos":[]},"section":{"sectionText":"","smallerSectionText":""},"freeform":{"content":[[{"type":"text","stretch":true,"fillArea":true,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"grey","placeholderInvisible":false,"useFigureAdditionalScale":false,"figureAdditionalScale":1,"span":4,"markdown":"Postnatal care for newborns shows persistent disruptions, averaging about 20% below expected levels, with July 2025 nearly 22% lower than expected.

Postnatal care for mothers also falls below expectations, averaging about 11% lower, with July 2025 around 13% lower, similarly reflecting incomplete reporting.

Across both indicators, the shaded shortfalls reflect a mix of service use and reporting disruptions, and the pattern appears to be driven largely by reporting completeness issues rather than true declines in postnatal care."},{"type":"figure","stretch":true,"fillArea":false,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"none","placeholderInvisible":false,"useFigureAdditionalScale":true,"figureAdditionalScale":1,"presentationObjectInReportInfo":{"id":"413db1fe-09e8-4b5e-b3d6-6316dc783df0","moduleId":"m003","selectedReplicantValue":"","isDefault":false}}]],"useHeader":true,"headerText":"Postnatal care shortfalls likely reporting-driven, with larger gaps for newborns"}}

{"type":"freeform","cover":{"titleText":"","subTitleText":"","presenterText":"","dateText":"","logos":[]},"section":{"sectionText":"","smallerSectionText":""},"freeform":{"content":[[{"type":"text","stretch":true,"fillArea":true,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"grey","placeholderInvisible":false,"useFigureAdditionalScale":false,"figureAdditionalScale":1,"span":4,"markdown":"ANC1 showed disruptions in mid-2025, with service use around 9–13% below expected levels (~64,000 vs. ~71,000 expected).

ANC4 largely tracked expected trends throughout the period, without notable disruptions.

Far fewer women progress from ANC1 to ANC4, underscoring a persistent continuity gap in antenatal care."},{"type":"figure","stretch":true,"fillArea":false,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"none","placeholderInvisible":false,"useFigureAdditionalScale":true,"figureAdditionalScale":1,"presentationObjectInReportInfo":{"id":"f13bc674-ef5d-4619-9723-9bf804e56ee5","moduleId":"m003","selectedReplicantValue":"","isDefault":false}}]],"useHeader":true,"headerText":"ANC service use aligns with expectations, though continuity gaps persist"}}

{"type":"freeform","cover":{"titleText":"","titleTextRelFontSize":10,"subTitleText":"","subTitleTextRelFontSize":6,"presenterText":"","presenterTextRelFontSize":4,"dateText":"","dateTextRelFontSize":3,"logos":[]},"section":{"sectionText":"","sectionTextRelFontSize":8,"smallerSectionText":"","smallerSectionTextRelFontSize":5},"freeform":{"content":[[{"type":"text","stretch":true,"fillArea":false,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"none","placeholderInvisible":false,"placeholderStretch":true,"placeholderHeight":50,"useFigureAdditionalScale":false,"figureAdditionalScale":1,"imgHeight":300,"imgFit":"inside","imgStretch":true,"hideFigureCaption":false,"hideFigureSubCaption":false,"hideFigureFootnote":false,"span":3,"markdown":"BCG volumes declined by 13.5% in Q1 2025, interrupting an otherwise steady trend through 2023 and 2024.

Both Penta1 and Penta3 experienced declines in Q1 2025, but Penta1 showed a stronger recovery the following quarter. Penta1 volumes rebounded by ~15% in Q2 2025 after a ~14% drop in Q1, while Penta3 rose more modestly following its ~11% decline.

These shifts highlight short-term fluctuations but suggest an overall recovery in immunization activity by mid-2025."},{"type":"figure","presentationObjectInReportInfo":{"id":"9f726f82-bcd8-46a2-a56c-ea5f3a03ba0f","moduleId":"m003","isDefault":false,"selectedReplicantValue":""},"stretch":true,"fillArea":false,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"none","placeholderInvisible":false,"placeholderStretch":true,"placeholderHeight":50,"useFigureAdditionalScale":false,"figureAdditionalScale":1,"imgHeight":300,"imgFit":"inside","imgStretch":true,"hideFigureCaption":false,"hideFigureSubCaption":false,"hideFigureFootnote":false}]],"useHeader":true,"headerText":"Quarter-to-quarter change in service volume child immunization"}}

{"type":"freeform","cover":{"titleText":"","subTitleText":"","presenterText":"","dateText":"","logos":[]},"section":{"sectionText":"","smallerSectionText":""},"freeform":{"content":[[{"type":"text","stretch":true,"fillArea":true,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"grey","placeholderInvisible":false,"useFigureAdditionalScale":false,"figureAdditionalScale":1,"span":4,"markdown":"Deliveries by skilled birth attendant showed two brief disruptions in late 2023 and mid-2024, when reported service use dipped below expected trends.

These disruptions are likely linked to changes in reporting rather than true declines in service delivery.

Overall, delivery volumes closely tracked expectations through mid-2025, reflecting steady service use with only temporary deviations."},{"type":"figure","stretch":true,"fillArea":false,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"none","placeholderInvisible":false,"useFigureAdditionalScale":true,"figureAdditionalScale":1,"presentationObjectInReportInfo":{"id":"a19b1433-440f-4123-a63a-c2bab8d4d86c","moduleId":"m003","selectedReplicantValue":"","isDefault":false}}]],"useHeader":true,"headerText":"Delivery volumes remain stable with only brief and limited disruptions"}}

{"type":"freeform","cover":{"titleText":"","titleTextRelFontSize":10,"subTitleText":"","subTitleTextRelFontSize":6,"presenterText":"","presenterTextRelFontSize":4,"dateText":"","dateTextRelFontSize":3,"logos":[]},"section":{"sectionText":"","sectionTextRelFontSize":8,"smallerSectionText":"","smallerSectionTextRelFontSize":5},"freeform":{"content":[[{"type":"text","stretch":true,"fillArea":false,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"none","placeholderInvisible":false,"placeholderStretch":true,"placeholderHeight":50,"useFigureAdditionalScale":false,"figureAdditionalScale":1,"imgHeight":300,"imgFit":"inside","imgStretch":true,"hideFigureCaption":false,"hideFigureSubCaption":false,"hideFigureFootnote":false,"span":3,"markdown":"Diagnoses of SAM declined sharply in the second half of 2023, falling from ~53,000 to below ~35,000 cases.

