"},{"type":"figure","presentationObjectInReportInfo":{"id":"ccc36db6-8b35-48fc-b981-21926d770aab","moduleId":"m003","isDefault":false,"selectedReplicantValue":""},"stretch":true,"fillArea":false,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"none","placeholderInvisible":false,"placeholderStretch":true,"placeholderHeight":50,"useFigureAdditionalScale":false,"figureAdditionalScale":1,"imgHeight":300,"imgFit":"inside","imgStretch":true,"hideFigureCaption":false,"hideFigureSubCaption":false,"hideFigureFootnote":false}]],"useHeader":true,"headerText":"Trends in children diagnosed with severe acute malnutrition (SAM)"}}

{"type":"freeform","cover":{"titleText":"","titleTextRelFontSize":10,"subTitleText":"","subTitleTextRelFontSize":6,"presenterText":"","presenterTextRelFontSize":4,"dateText":"","dateTextRelFontSize":3,"logos":[]},"section":{"sectionText":"","sectionTextRelFontSize":8,"smallerSectionText":"","smallerSectionTextRelFontSize":5},"freeform":{"content":[[{"type":"text","stretch":true,"fillArea":false,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"none","placeholderInvisible":false,"placeholderStretch":true,"placeholderHeight":50,"useFigureAdditionalScale":false,"figureAdditionalScale":1,"imgHeight":300,"imgFit":"inside","imgStretch":true,"hideFigureCaption":false,"hideFigureSubCaption":false,"hideFigureFootnote":false,"span":3,"markdown":"ACT treatments for confirmed malaria cases showed only slight increases over time, remaining below 2,500 per month. Testing through microscopy followed a similar flat trend, with minor fluctuations but no sustained growth.

RDT testing volumes were higher and more variable, declining through 2024 before rebounding sharply in early 2025 and then easing slightly by mid-year.

The trend in ACT treatments appears to loosely follow microscopy testing volumes, though at  lower levels, suggesting only partial alignment between all confirmed cases and treatment patterns."},{"type":"figure","presentationObjectInReportInfo":{"id":"7e209620-ee34-4500-a376-bc4399347660","moduleId":"m003","isDefault":false,"selectedReplicantValue":""},"stretch":true,"fillArea":false,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"none","placeholderInvisible":false,"placeholderStretch":true,"placeholderHeight":50,"useFigureAdditionalScale":false,"figureAdditionalScale":1,"imgHeight":300,"imgFit":"inside","imgStretch":true,"hideFigureCaption":false,"hideFigureSubCaption":false,"hideFigureFootnote":false}]],"useHeader":true,"headerText":"Trends in malaria"}}

{"type":"freeform","cover":{"titleText":"","subTitleText":"","presenterText":"","dateText":"","logos":[]},"section":{"sectionText":"","smallerSectionText":""},"freeform":{"content":[[{"type":"text","stretch":true,"fillArea":true,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"grey","placeholderInvisible":false,"useFigureAdditionalScale":false,"figureAdditionalScale":1,"span":4,"markdown":"BCG: Multiple sustained disruptions through 2023–2025, with service use ~10–20% below expected levels during shaded periods. After accounting for reporting completeness, the disruption in 2025 stands out as a real service decline.

Penta1: Brief disruptions in 2023 and early 2025, with dips of ~5–10% below expected levels.

